1
00:02:38,385 --> 00:02:40,046
There's a very
pretty young woman

2
00:02:40,153 --> 00:02:42,212
crossing the street

3
00:02:42,322 --> 00:02:45,689
and I think she
may be coming here.

4
00:02:45,792 --> 00:02:47,589
Incidentally, I
have glanced over

5
00:02:47,694 --> 00:02:49,457
your latest
account of my work.

6
00:02:49,563 --> 00:02:51,497
Oh yes.

7
00:02:51,598 --> 00:02:54,499
Honestly I cannot
congratulate you upon it.

8
00:02:57,337 --> 00:03:01,671
Detection is, or ought
to be, an exact science.

9
00:03:01,775 --> 00:03:03,766
Observation deduction

10
00:03:03,877 --> 00:03:06,038
a cold and
unemotional subject.

11
00:03:06,146 --> 00:03:08,171
You have attempted
to tinge it
with romanticism,

12
00:03:08,281 --> 00:03:09,475
which has much
the same effect

13
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,073
as if you worked a
love-story or an

14
00:03:11,184 --> 00:03:14,813
elopement into the fifth
proposition of Euclid.

15
00:03:14,921 --> 00:03:18,084
Who can match that?

16
00:03:18,191 --> 00:03:21,524
There's a young lady
to see you Mr. Holmes.

17
00:03:23,997 --> 00:03:25,589
It's Mary Morstan.

18
00:03:25,699 --> 00:03:27,724
I have no recollection
of the name.

19
00:03:30,537 --> 00:03:33,233
Don't go Doctor,
I may need you.

20
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:35,308
I was right.

21
00:03:38,745 --> 00:03:40,406
Thank you.

22
00:03:40,513 --> 00:03:41,775
Miss Morstan.

23
00:03:41,882 --> 00:03:43,645
Good afternoon.

24
00:03:48,588 --> 00:03:49,919
I have come to
you Mr. Holmes

25
00:03:50,023 --> 00:03:52,014
because you once
enabled my employer,

26
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,717
Mrs. Cecil Forrester,

27
00:03:53,827 --> 00:03:56,887
to unravel a minor
domestic complication.

28
00:03:56,997 --> 00:03:58,396
She was much impressed

29
00:03:58,498 --> 00:04:01,365
with your kindness
and skill.

30
00:04:01,468 --> 00:04:03,095
Thank you.

31
00:04:15,081 --> 00:04:17,413
I can hardly imagine
anything more strange,

32
00:04:17,517 --> 00:04:20,577
more utterly
inexplicable,

33
00:04:20,687 --> 00:04:22,882
than the situation in
which I find myself.

34
00:04:22,989 --> 00:04:25,514
State your case.

35
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,217
You will, I am
sure, excuse me.

36
00:04:27,327 --> 00:04:30,956
If your friend would be
good enough to remain,

37
00:04:31,064 --> 00:04:33,794
he might be of
inestimable service to me.

38
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,492
Of course.

39
00:04:45,312 --> 00:04:49,646
Briefly the
facts are these.

40
00:04:49,749 --> 00:04:53,310
My father was an officer
in an Indian regiment.

41
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:56,753
My mother died when I
was still quite a child

42
00:04:56,856 --> 00:05:00,155
and he was forced
to send me home,

43
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:03,627
despite the fact that I
had no relatives here.

44
00:05:03,730 --> 00:05:05,129
I was placed in a

45
00:05:05,231 --> 00:05:06,892
comfortable boarding
establishment

46
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,695
at Edinburgh, and
I remained there

47
00:05:08,802 --> 00:05:10,565
until I was 1 7
years of age.

48
00:05:10,670 --> 00:05:14,037
In that same
year my father,

49
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:18,236
who was a senior
captain of his regiment,

50
00:05:18,345 --> 00:05:24,341
obtained 12 months'
leave and returned home.

51
00:05:24,451 --> 00:05:25,941
He telegraphed to me
from London to say

52
00:05:26,052 --> 00:05:28,111
that he had
arrived all safe

53
00:05:28,221 --> 00:05:30,280
and directed me to
come down at once,

54
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:33,985
giving the Langham
Hotel as his address.

55
00:05:34,094 --> 00:05:37,063
His message,
as I remember,

56
00:05:37,163 --> 00:05:40,758
was full of love
and kindness.

57
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:42,232
On reaching London

58
00:05:42,335 --> 00:05:44,132
I drove straight to
the Langham Hotel

59
00:05:44,237 --> 00:05:46,228
and was informed
that Captain Morstan

60
00:05:46,339 --> 00:05:48,000
was staying there,

61
00:05:48,108 --> 00:05:49,598
but that he had gone
out the night before

62
00:05:49,709 --> 00:05:51,836
and had not returned.

63
00:05:51,945 --> 00:05:56,006
So I waited

64
00:05:56,116 --> 00:05:58,607
all day

65
00:05:58,718 --> 00:06:03,178
without news of him.

66
00:06:03,289 --> 00:06:07,316
And that night,

67
00:06:07,427 --> 00:06:12,262
on the advice of the
manager of the hotel,

68
00:06:12,365 --> 00:06:17,632
I communicated
with the police,

69
00:06:17,737 --> 00:06:19,170
the next day
we advertised

70
00:06:19,272 --> 00:06:23,231
in all the newspapers.

71
00:06:23,343 --> 00:06:26,506
Our inquiries
led to no result

72
00:06:26,613 --> 00:06:28,945
from that day to this

73
00:06:29,049 --> 00:06:30,778
no word has
ever been heard

74
00:06:30,884 --> 00:06:33,250
of my unfortunate
father.

75
00:06:41,795 --> 00:06:44,992
He came home with his
heart so full of hope

76
00:06:45,098 --> 00:06:46,656
to find some peace,

77
00:06:46,766 --> 00:06:48,666
some comfort,

78
00:06:48,768 --> 00:06:50,759
and instead

79
00:06:57,944 --> 00:07:01,107
The date?

80
00:07:01,214 --> 00:07:02,340
The 3rd of December

81
00:07:02,449 --> 00:07:07,216
exactly 1 0 years ago.

82
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:09,447
His luggage?

83
00:07:09,556 --> 00:07:13,287
Remained at the hotel.

84
00:07:13,393 --> 00:07:15,725
Oh there was nothing in
it to suggest a clue --

85
00:07:15,829 --> 00:07:18,093
some clothes, some books,

86
00:07:18,198 --> 00:07:20,063
and a considerable
number of curiosities

87
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:22,600
from the
Andaman Islands.

88
00:07:25,371 --> 00:07:26,770
My father had been
one of the officers

89
00:07:26,873 --> 00:07:28,431
in charge of the
convict-guard there.

90
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,133
Watson this
place is a mess.

91
00:07:30,243 --> 00:07:31,904
Had he any
friends in town?

92
00:07:32,011 --> 00:07:34,502
Only one that
we know of

93
00:07:34,614 --> 00:07:37,412
Major Sholto, of
his old regiment,

94
00:07:37,517 --> 00:07:40,714
the 34th Bombay
Infantry.

95
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:43,288
We communicated with
the Major, of course,

96
00:07:43,389 --> 00:07:46,290
but he did not
seem to know

97
00:07:46,392 --> 00:07:48,326
that his brother
officer was in England.

98
00:07:48,428 --> 00:07:50,225
It's a singular case.

99
00:07:56,469 --> 00:07:59,734
I have not yet
communicated to you

100
00:07:59,839 --> 00:08:02,171
the most singular part.

101
00:08:04,277 --> 00:08:05,574
4 years later

102
00:08:05,678 --> 00:08:07,509
an advertisement had
appeared in the Times

103
00:08:07,614 --> 00:08:09,514
asking for the address
of Miss Mary Morstan,

104
00:08:09,616 --> 00:08:11,481
and stating that it
would be to her advantage

105
00:08:11,584 --> 00:08:13,745
to come forward.

106
00:08:13,853 --> 00:08:16,879
There was no
name appended.

107
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:18,321
I had at the time

108
00:08:18,424 --> 00:08:20,415
just entered the family
of Mrs. Cecil Forrester

109
00:08:20,527 --> 00:08:22,256
in the capacity
of governess

110
00:08:22,362 --> 00:08:24,387
and on her advice I
published my address

111
00:08:24,497 --> 00:08:27,432
in the advertisement
column.

112
00:08:27,534 --> 00:08:29,934
That same day there
appeared through the post

113
00:08:30,036 --> 00:08:34,803
a small cardboard
box addressed to me,

114
00:08:34,908 --> 00:08:37,001
which I found to contain

115
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:40,443
a very large and
lustrous pearl.

116
00:08:40,547 --> 00:08:42,845
No word of writing
was enclosed.

117
00:08:42,949 --> 00:08:46,476
And since then every
year upon the same date

118
00:08:46,586 --> 00:08:48,611
there has always
appeared a similar box,

119
00:08:48,721 --> 00:08:50,154
containing a
similar pearl,

120
00:08:50,256 --> 00:08:52,781
with no clue as
to the sender.

121
00:08:52,892 --> 00:08:54,359
They have been
pronounced by an expert

122
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:56,121
to be of a rare variety

123
00:08:56,229 --> 00:09:00,256
and of considerable value.

124
00:09:00,366 --> 00:09:01,663
You can see for yourself

125
00:09:01,768 --> 00:09:04,896
that they are
very handsome.

126
00:09:11,778 --> 00:09:16,442
Your case is
most interesting.

127
00:09:16,549 --> 00:09:19,074
Something else has
occurred to you?

128
00:09:19,185 --> 00:09:22,018
Yes, and no
later than today.

129
00:09:22,121 --> 00:09:25,318
That is why I
have come to you.

130
00:09:25,425 --> 00:09:29,555
This letter
arrived through the
post this morning,

131
00:09:29,662 --> 00:09:32,688
which you will perhaps
read for yourself.

132
00:09:32,799 --> 00:09:35,097
Envelope please.

133
00:09:37,103 --> 00:09:39,697
London postmark,
October 7th.

134
00:09:39,806 --> 00:09:42,707
Man's thumb
mark on corner

135
00:09:42,809 --> 00:09:46,472
probably the postman.

136
00:09:46,579 --> 00:09:47,944
Best quality paper.

137
00:09:48,047 --> 00:09:49,878
Sixpence a packet.

138
00:09:49,983 --> 00:09:52,508
Particular man in
his stationery.

139
00:09:52,619 --> 00:09:54,712
Watson.

140
00:09:54,821 --> 00:09:58,018
Be at the third
pillar from the left

141
00:09:58,124 --> 00:09:59,751
outside the
Lyceum Theatre

142
00:09:59,859 --> 00:10:01,690
tonight at
seven o'clock.

143
00:10:01,794 --> 00:10:03,955
If you are distrustful
bring 2 friends.

144
00:10:04,063 --> 00:10:07,464
You are a wronged woman
and shall have justice.

145
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:08,864
Do not bring the police.

146
00:10:08,968 --> 00:10:10,663
If you do, all
will be in vain.

147
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:12,397
Your unknown friend.

148
00:10:12,505 --> 00:10:13,836
Well, really,

149
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:15,339
this is a very pretty
little problem.

150
00:10:15,441 --> 00:10:16,874
What do you intend
to do, Miss Morstan?

151
00:10:16,976 --> 00:10:18,534
Well that is exactly
what I want to ask you.

152
00:10:18,645 --> 00:10:20,909
Well then you and I
shall go together.

153
00:10:21,014 --> 00:10:22,914
Dr. Watson is
the very man.

154
00:10:23,016 --> 00:10:26,281
Your correspondent
says 2 friends.

155
00:10:26,386 --> 00:10:28,149
But would he come?

156
00:10:28,254 --> 00:10:29,653
I shall be proud and happy

157
00:10:29,756 --> 00:10:32,486
if I can be
of any service.

158
00:10:32,592 --> 00:10:34,719
You are both very kind.

159
00:10:34,827 --> 00:10:35,919
I have led a retired life

160
00:10:36,029 --> 00:10:38,759
and have no friends
whom I could appeal to.

161
00:10:38,865 --> 00:10:40,924
If I am here at 6 it
will do, I suppose?

162
00:10:41,034 --> 00:10:42,467
Yes but you must
not be later.

163
00:10:42,568 --> 00:10:44,126
Goodbye Miss Morstan.

164
00:10:44,237 --> 00:10:46,296
Goodbye Mr. Holmes.

165
00:10:46,406 --> 00:10:47,668
Au revoir.

166
00:10:47,774 --> 00:10:49,173
Au revoir.

167
00:11:03,122 --> 00:11:05,283
Buy a flower dearie.

168
00:11:05,391 --> 00:11:07,256
Buy a flower.

169
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,590
Aw come on dearie.

170
00:11:09,696 --> 00:11:12,494
Excuse me.

171
00:11:12,598 --> 00:11:16,796
What a very
attractive woman

172
00:11:16,903 --> 00:11:18,200
It is of the
first importance

173
00:11:18,304 --> 00:11:19,703
not to allow your
judgment to be biased

174
00:11:19,806 --> 00:11:21,467
by personal qualities.

175
00:11:21,574 --> 00:11:23,098
A client to me
is a mere unit,

176
00:11:23,209 --> 00:11:24,608
a factor in of
the problem.

177
00:11:24,711 --> 00:11:26,872
Holmes, you are
a automaton

178
00:11:26,979 --> 00:11:28,606
and a calculating
machine.

179
00:11:28,715 --> 00:11:31,275
There's something
positively inhuman
in you at times.

180
00:11:31,384 --> 00:11:32,510
I assure you

181
00:11:32,618 --> 00:11:34,176
the most winning
woman I ever knew

182
00:11:34,287 --> 00:11:36,221
was hanged for poisoning
3 little children

183
00:11:36,322 --> 00:11:38,256
for their
insurance money,

184
00:11:38,358 --> 00:11:40,622
and the most repellent
man of my acquaintance

185
00:11:40,727 --> 00:11:42,922
is a philanthropist
who has spent nearly

186
00:11:43,029 --> 00:11:45,088
a quarter of a million
upon the London poor.

187
00:11:45,198 --> 00:11:47,723
However, in this case,

188
00:11:47,834 --> 00:11:49,392
I never make exceptions.

189
00:11:49,502 --> 00:11:50,901
An exception
disproves the rule.

190
00:11:51,003 --> 00:11:52,937
I'm going out. I'll
see you in an hour.

191
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:09,845
<i>Had he any
friends in town?</i>

192
00:12:09,956 --> 00:12:12,584
<i>Only one that
we know of,</i>

193
00:12:12,692 --> 00:12:15,889
<i>Major Sholto of
his own regiment.</i>

194
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:25,597
There is no great
mystery in this matter

195
00:12:25,705 --> 00:12:27,673
the facts appear to admit
of only one explanation.

196
00:12:27,774 --> 00:12:29,674
Oh so you've
solved it already?

197
00:12:29,776 --> 00:12:31,073
I have found,

198
00:12:31,177 --> 00:12:32,542
on consulting the back
files of the Times,

199
00:12:32,645 --> 00:12:34,135
that Major Sholto,
of Upper Norwood,

200
00:12:34,247 --> 00:12:35,908
late of the 34th
Bombay Infantry,

201
00:12:36,015 --> 00:12:39,348
died just 6 years ago.

202
00:12:39,452 --> 00:12:42,182
Mrs. Hudson you're
dreadfully under foot.

203
00:12:43,389 --> 00:12:44,583
I may be very
obtuse, Holmes,

204
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:45,987
but I fail to see
what this suggests.

205
00:12:46,092 --> 00:12:47,286
Really?

206
00:12:47,393 --> 00:12:48,655
You surprise me.

207
00:12:48,761 --> 00:12:49,989
Now look at it
this way, then.

208
00:12:50,096 --> 00:12:51,825
Captain Morstan
disappears.

209
00:12:51,931 --> 00:12:53,330
The only person in London

210
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:55,401
whom he could have
visited is Major Sholto.

211
00:12:55,501 --> 00:12:56,900
Major Sholto denies
having heard

212
00:12:57,003 --> 00:12:58,664
that he was
even in London.

213
00:12:58,771 --> 00:13:00,739
4 years later Sholto dies.

214
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:03,331
Within a week of his death

215
00:13:03,443 --> 00:13:04,876
Captain Morstan's daughter

216
00:13:04,977 --> 00:13:06,467
receives a
valuable present,

217
00:13:06,579 --> 00:13:08,240
which is repeated
from year to year

218
00:13:08,347 --> 00:13:10,110
and now culminates
in a letter,

219
00:13:10,216 --> 00:13:12,912
which describes her
as a wronged woman.

220
00:13:13,019 --> 00:13:15,078
Now what wrong can
it possibly refer to

221
00:13:15,188 --> 00:13:18,248
except this deprivation
of her father?

222
00:13:18,357 --> 00:13:20,120
Tape measure,

223
00:13:20,226 --> 00:13:21,818
gun.

224
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,156
And why should
these presents

225
00:13:25,264 --> 00:13:26,595
begin immediately
after Sholto's death

226
00:13:26,699 --> 00:13:29,224
unless it is that
Sholto's heir

227
00:13:29,335 --> 00:13:30,529
knows something
of the mystery

228
00:13:30,636 --> 00:13:32,695
and desires to
make compensation?

229
00:13:35,107 --> 00:13:37,234
Are you ready Watson?

230
00:13:37,343 --> 00:13:39,777
And waiting.

231
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,210
Have you any
alternative theory

232
00:13:41,314 --> 00:13:42,747
that will meet the facts?

233
00:13:42,849 --> 00:13:44,146
But what a strange
compensation!

234
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:45,774
And how strangely made!

235
00:13:45,885 --> 00:13:47,443
What time is it?

236
00:13:47,553 --> 00:13:49,578
It's a quarter
past the hour.

237
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,361
Evening Ellis.

238
00:14:02,468 --> 00:14:03,457
Evening sir.

239
00:14:05,471 --> 00:14:06,733
Why should somebody

240
00:14:06,839 --> 00:14:08,101
write her a letter now,

241
00:14:08,207 --> 00:14:09,799
rather than 6 years ago?

242
00:14:09,909 --> 00:14:12,104
Again, the letter speaks
of giving her justice.

243
00:14:12,211 --> 00:14:13,439
What justice can she have?

244
00:14:13,546 --> 00:14:14,740
It is too much to suppose

245
00:14:14,847 --> 00:14:16,280
that her father
is still alive

246
00:14:16,382 --> 00:14:17,781
and there's no
other injustice

247
00:14:17,884 --> 00:14:19,476
in her case that
you know of.

248
00:14:19,585 --> 00:14:21,519
There are difficulties

249
00:14:21,621 --> 00:14:23,851
but there are
always difficulties.

250
00:14:28,728 --> 00:14:29,592
Good evening Mr Holmes.

251
00:14:29,695 --> 00:14:30,662
I do hope I'm not...

252
00:14:30,763 --> 00:14:31,422
Good evening.

253
00:14:40,139 --> 00:14:41,163
By the way,

254
00:14:41,274 --> 00:14:43,401
a curious paper was
found in Papa's desk,

255
00:14:43,509 --> 00:14:45,977
which nobody
could understand.

256
00:14:46,078 --> 00:14:47,875
I don't suppose it is of
the slightest importance,

257
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:50,107
but I thought you
might like to see it,

258
00:14:50,216 --> 00:14:53,049
so I brought it with me.

259
00:14:53,152 --> 00:14:55,620
The paper appears to be
of Indian manufacture.

260
00:14:55,721 --> 00:15:00,420
At some point it's
been pinned to a board.

261
00:15:00,526 --> 00:15:03,051
The diagram upon it
appears to be the plan

262
00:15:03,162 --> 00:15:05,255
of part of a
large building

263
00:15:05,364 --> 00:15:09,562
with numerous halls,
corridors, and passages.

264
00:15:09,669 --> 00:15:12,934
There's a cross
in red ink,

265
00:15:13,039 --> 00:15:17,373
and on the side is
written '3.37 from left.'

266
00:15:17,476 --> 00:15:20,809
There is a curious
hieroglyphic,

267
00:15:20,913 --> 00:15:23,939
The sign of four

268
00:15:24,050 --> 00:15:25,847
Kartar Singh,
Indrajit Singh,

269
00:15:25,952 --> 00:15:28,716
Jagodish Singh,
Jonathan Small.

270
00:15:28,821 --> 00:15:31,984
It appears it has
been kept carefully
in a pocketbook,

271
00:15:32,091 --> 00:15:34,651
for the one side is
as clean as the other.

272
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:37,991
It was in his pocketbook
that we found it.

273
00:15:38,097 --> 00:15:41,066
Preserve it carefully,
Miss Morstan.

274
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,567
I begin to suspect
that this case may be

275
00:15:43,669 --> 00:15:45,227
much deeper
and more subtle

276
00:15:45,338 --> 00:15:47,932
than I ever
first supposed.

277
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:33,215
Hey, are you the parties

278
00:16:33,319 --> 00:16:35,184
who come with
Miss Morstan?

279
00:16:35,287 --> 00:16:36,549
I'm Miss Morstan,

280
00:16:36,656 --> 00:16:38,487
and these 2 gentlemen
are my companions.

281
00:16:38,591 --> 00:16:40,582
I must ask you to
give me your word

282
00:16:40,693 --> 00:16:42,251
that neither of
your companions

283
00:16:42,361 --> 00:16:43,760
is a police officer.

284
00:16:43,863 --> 00:16:45,854
I give you my word.

285
00:17:23,269 --> 00:17:26,568
Sahib awaits you.

286
00:17:26,672 --> 00:17:28,537
Show them in, Khitmutgar.

287
00:17:28,641 --> 00:17:30,700
Show them
straight in to me.

288
00:17:35,047 --> 00:17:39,143
Your servant,
Miss Morstan.

289
00:17:39,251 --> 00:17:41,048
Your servant, gentlemen.

290
00:17:41,153 --> 00:17:43,053
Come in.

291
00:17:43,155 --> 00:17:43,814
Come in.

292
00:17:43,923 --> 00:17:44,787
Come in.

293
00:17:44,890 --> 00:17:48,257
Come in to my
little sanctum.

294
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:50,794
I trust you have
no objection

295
00:17:50,896 --> 00:17:54,593
to tobacco smoke?

296
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,793
The balsamic odor

297
00:17:56,902 --> 00:17:59,962
of Eastern tobacco?

298
00:18:00,072 --> 00:18:03,166
I am a little nervous

299
00:18:03,275 --> 00:18:08,303
and I find my hookah
to be an invaluable...

300
00:18:21,694 --> 00:18:23,218
sedative.

301
00:18:26,031 --> 00:18:28,898
You will excuse
me Mr. Sholto

302
00:18:29,001 --> 00:18:31,299
but I am here
at your request

303
00:18:31,403 --> 00:18:32,870
to learn something,

304
00:18:32,972 --> 00:18:34,997
which you desire
to tell me?

305
00:18:35,107 --> 00:18:37,132
It is getting very
late and I should wish

306
00:18:37,243 --> 00:18:39,575
the interview to be
as short as possible.

307
00:18:41,714 --> 00:18:44,774
Well it must
take some time.

308
00:18:44,884 --> 00:18:49,912
For we have to
go to Norwood

309
00:18:50,022 --> 00:18:54,322
to see brother
Bartholomew.

310
00:18:54,426 --> 00:19:00,058
We must all see

311
00:19:00,166 --> 00:19:03,033
if we can get the better

312
00:19:03,135 --> 00:19:07,663
of brother
Bartholomew.

313
00:19:07,773 --> 00:19:11,368
He is angry with me for

314
00:19:11,477 --> 00:19:17,438
taking the course that
has seemed right to me.

315
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:19,643
You cannot imagine

316
00:19:19,752 --> 00:19:23,779
what a terrible
fellow he is

317
00:19:23,889 --> 00:19:28,155
when he is angry.

318
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:29,887
If we are to
go to Norwood,

319
00:19:29,995 --> 00:19:31,326
it would
perhaps be as well

320
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:32,727
if we were start at once.

321
00:19:32,832 --> 00:19:34,060
No.

322
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:36,726
No that would hardly do.

323
00:19:36,836 --> 00:19:38,167
I don't know what
he would say

324
00:19:38,270 --> 00:19:40,363
if we came upon him
in that sudden way.

325
00:19:40,472 --> 00:19:42,940
No I must prepare you

326
00:19:43,042 --> 00:19:47,172
by showing you
where we all stand

327
00:19:47,279 --> 00:19:50,214
to each other.

328
00:19:50,316 --> 00:19:57,745
I must lay the
facts before you,

329
00:19:57,857 --> 00:20:01,054
as I know them myself.

330
00:20:05,731 --> 00:20:11,226
My father, the late
Major John Sholto,

331
00:20:11,337 --> 00:20:15,205
came to live at
Pondicherry Lodge

332
00:20:15,307 --> 00:20:17,673
in Upper Norwood

333
00:20:17,776 --> 00:20:21,940
some 1 1 years ago.

334
00:20:22,047 --> 00:20:25,016
And he had
prospered in India

335
00:20:25,117 --> 00:20:27,415
and brought back with him

336
00:20:27,519 --> 00:20:29,851
a considerable
sum of money,

337
00:20:29,955 --> 00:20:33,049
a collection of
valuable curiosities,

338
00:20:33,158 --> 00:20:36,685
and a staff of
native servants.

339
00:20:36,795 --> 00:20:38,763
With these advantages

340
00:20:38,864 --> 00:20:41,628
he lived in great luxury.

341
00:20:41,734 --> 00:20:45,101
My brother and I were at
university at the time.

342
00:20:45,204 --> 00:20:47,604
We did know, however,

343
00:20:47,706 --> 00:20:49,264
that some mystery,

344
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:51,639
some positive danger,

345
00:20:51,744 --> 00:20:54,679
overhung our father.

346
00:20:56,849 --> 00:20:59,283
He was very fearful

347
00:20:59,385 --> 00:21:01,910
of going out alone,

348
00:21:02,021 --> 00:21:05,479
and he employed
2 prizefighters

349
00:21:05,591 --> 00:21:06,990
to guard him.

350
00:21:07,092 --> 00:21:09,822
Williams, who drove
you here tonight,

351
00:21:09,929 --> 00:21:11,726
was one of them.

352
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:13,297
For some reason,

353
00:21:13,399 --> 00:21:15,026
he never told anyone,

354
00:21:15,134 --> 00:21:16,897
my father had a
marked aversion

355
00:21:17,002 --> 00:21:20,529
to men with wooden legs.

356
00:21:20,639 --> 00:21:22,004
On one occasion

357
00:21:22,107 --> 00:21:24,234
he actually fired
his revolver

358
00:21:24,343 --> 00:21:27,312
at a one-legged man.

359
00:21:27,413 --> 00:21:31,281
A harmless tradesman
as it turned out.

360
00:21:37,923 --> 00:21:39,447
I remember we
have to pay

361
00:21:39,558 --> 00:21:42,891
a considerable sum
to hush it up.

362
00:21:44,663 --> 00:21:47,530
Then suddenly

363
00:21:49,702 --> 00:21:53,536
my father
received a letter

364
00:21:55,007 --> 00:21:58,966
It was a great
shock to him.

365
00:22:10,055 --> 00:22:11,784
Out.

366
00:22:11,890 --> 00:22:13,721
Out of the room!

367
00:22:13,826 --> 00:22:16,386
Out of the room!

368
00:22:29,508 --> 00:22:34,275
What was in the letter

369
00:22:34,380 --> 00:22:38,612
we could never discover?

370
00:22:38,717 --> 00:22:42,050
For years my father
had suffered

371
00:22:42,154 --> 00:22:44,816
with an
enlarged spleen

372
00:22:44,923 --> 00:22:46,720
and from that moment on

373
00:22:46,825 --> 00:22:49,521
he became rapidly worse.

374
00:22:49,628 --> 00:22:54,497
But one night the
doctor informed us
there was no hope

375
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:58,161
and that he wished
to make a last
communication to us.

376
00:23:01,540 --> 00:23:03,770
My dear family,

377
00:23:08,047 --> 00:23:10,845
when we were in India

378
00:23:10,949 --> 00:23:15,079
my friend, Morstan and I,

379
00:23:15,187 --> 00:23:17,519
came into possession

380
00:23:17,623 --> 00:23:21,582
of a considerable
treasure.

381
00:23:21,693 --> 00:23:27,290
I brought it home
with me to this house,

382
00:23:27,399 --> 00:23:29,367
where it's still alive.

383
00:23:33,405 --> 00:23:37,034
On the day, Mr. Morstan,

384
00:23:37,142 --> 00:23:40,441
had arrived home
from the East.

385
00:23:40,546 --> 00:23:45,643
He came straight
to this house

386
00:23:45,751 --> 00:23:49,346
to claim his share.

387
00:23:49,455 --> 00:23:51,480
We gave our word Sholto.

388
00:23:51,590 --> 00:23:52,784
A promise.

389
00:23:52,891 --> 00:23:55,155
We gave our word
and our oath.

390
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:57,455
another time,

391
00:23:57,563 --> 00:23:59,190
another life,
another world,

392
00:23:59,298 --> 00:24:01,095
a solemn promise.

393
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,634
You tried to
betray me Morstan.

394
00:24:03,735 --> 00:24:10,106
If you dare to
cross me...

395
00:24:10,209 --> 00:24:12,302
My God.

396
00:24:12,411 --> 00:24:14,538
The man is dead Altada.

397
00:24:14,646 --> 00:24:16,238
You have nothing
to fear Sir.

398
00:24:16,348 --> 00:24:18,213
I will arrange everything.

399
00:24:18,317 --> 00:24:22,151
And soon it was
done Miss Morstan,

400
00:24:22,254 --> 00:24:24,916
in secrecy of course

401
00:24:25,023 --> 00:24:27,856
but with respect.

402
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:30,360
This is disgraceful
Mister Sholto.

403
00:24:30,462 --> 00:24:33,022
Your father's behavior
was quite unforgivable.

404
00:24:33,132 --> 00:24:35,532
Please Doctor.

405
00:24:38,203 --> 00:24:39,500
I knew in my heart

406
00:24:39,605 --> 00:24:41,573
that he was dead.

407
00:24:44,076 --> 00:24:46,237
My father was
not alone then.

408
00:24:49,648 --> 00:24:52,242
And I'm glad he
didn't suffer.

409
00:24:52,351 --> 00:24:55,252
You're very brave
Miss Morstan.

410
00:24:55,354 --> 00:24:56,719
What concerns me now

411
00:24:56,822 --> 00:24:59,086
is the wishing
for this quarrel.

412
00:24:59,191 --> 00:25:00,920
I cannot imagine
how my father

413
00:25:01,026 --> 00:25:03,517
came to be involved
with that treasure.

414
00:25:03,629 --> 00:25:08,123
I'm afraid that is
not clear Miss Morstan

415
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:10,929
I can only tell you

416
00:25:11,036 --> 00:25:14,563
my father's instructions
concerning it.

417
00:25:26,118 --> 00:25:28,018
The greed.

418
00:25:29,521 --> 00:25:31,011
accursed greed
that has been

419
00:25:31,123 --> 00:25:33,717
my besetting thing
throughout my life

420
00:25:33,825 --> 00:25:37,784
has robbed her
of the treasure.

421
00:25:37,896 --> 00:25:40,865
Half of which, at least,

422
00:25:40,966 --> 00:25:43,867
should be hers.

423
00:25:43,969 --> 00:25:53,503
You see that
chaplet there.

424
00:25:53,612 --> 00:25:59,710
I had the design of
sending it to her

425
00:25:59,818 --> 00:26:06,815
but could not bear
to part with it.

426
00:26:06,925 --> 00:26:08,756
You

427
00:26:08,860 --> 00:26:11,158
my sons

428
00:26:11,263 --> 00:26:13,254
must see that
Miss Morstan

429
00:26:13,365 --> 00:26:17,768
gets her share
of the treasure.

430
00:26:30,916 --> 00:26:33,749
Get him away.

431
00:26:33,852 --> 00:26:37,811
For Christ's sake
get him away.

432
00:26:37,923 --> 00:26:41,188
We ran to the window
and out into the garden

433
00:26:41,293 --> 00:26:44,421
but the intruder was gone.

434
00:26:44,529 --> 00:26:47,396
My father was dead.

435
00:26:47,499 --> 00:26:51,902
We soon had more striking
proof that there were

436
00:26:52,004 --> 00:26:55,030
secret agencies that
work all around us.

437
00:26:55,140 --> 00:27:00,407
The next day my father's
bedroom was broken into

438
00:27:00,512 --> 00:27:06,508
and this was fixed
to his chest.

439
00:27:08,787 --> 00:27:10,778
Remarkable.

440
00:27:10,889 --> 00:27:14,552
It is the Sikkh symbol
for the numeral 4.

441
00:27:18,463 --> 00:27:20,158
What the paper means

442
00:27:20,265 --> 00:27:22,665
and who our secret
visitor or visitors were

443
00:27:22,768 --> 00:27:25,362
we never found out.

444
00:27:30,309 --> 00:27:32,937
And my brother and
I were much excited

445
00:27:33,045 --> 00:27:34,740
as you could imagine

446
00:27:34,846 --> 00:27:36,541
of the treasure that
my father had spoken

447
00:27:36,648 --> 00:27:38,548
but try as we might
we couldn't find it.

448
00:27:38,650 --> 00:27:40,447
It was maddened to think
that the hiding place

449
00:27:40,552 --> 00:27:43,715
was on his very
lips when he died.

450
00:27:43,822 --> 00:27:47,656
We could judge the
splendor of the riches

451
00:27:47,759 --> 00:27:49,818
by the chaplet, which
he had taken out.

452
00:27:49,928 --> 00:27:52,123
The pearls were
evidently of great value,

453
00:27:52,230 --> 00:27:56,496
and my brother was averse
to part with them,

454
00:27:56,601 --> 00:27:59,035
for, between friends,

455
00:27:59,137 --> 00:28:03,005
he was a little inclined
to my father's fault.

456
00:28:03,108 --> 00:28:05,372
And it was all I could
do was to persuade him

457
00:28:05,477 --> 00:28:07,775
to allow me to
send Miss Morstan

458
00:28:07,879 --> 00:28:10,871
a detached pearl at
regular intervals

459
00:28:10,982 --> 00:28:13,974
so that she would
not feel destitute.

460
00:28:14,086 --> 00:28:16,850
It was a kindly thought.

461
00:28:16,955 --> 00:28:21,551
No it was very
good of you.

462
00:28:21,660 --> 00:28:24,185
We were your trustees

463
00:28:24,296 --> 00:28:26,093
that was the way
I looked at it,

464
00:28:26,198 --> 00:28:27,893
although my brother

465
00:28:27,999 --> 00:28:29,660
did not altogether
see it in that light.

466
00:28:29,768 --> 00:28:32,601
We had plenty of
money ourselves.

467
00:28:32,704 --> 00:28:36,435
It would have been
in such bad taste

468
00:28:36,541 --> 00:28:39,339
to have treated
a young lady

469
00:28:39,444 --> 00:28:42,777
in so scurvy a fashion.

470
00:28:44,249 --> 00:28:46,513
Yesterday an event

471
00:28:46,618 --> 00:28:50,213
of extreme
importance occurred.

472
00:28:54,526 --> 00:28:58,690
We, found of
the treasure.

473
00:28:58,797 --> 00:29:03,200
Hence my instant
communication to
you Miss Morstan.

474
00:29:03,301 --> 00:29:06,759
Now all we have to do
is to drive to Norwood

475
00:29:06,872 --> 00:29:09,602
and claim our share.

476
00:29:12,611 --> 00:29:15,341
We shall be expected,

477
00:29:15,447 --> 00:29:19,611
if not entirely
welcome, visitors.

478
00:29:19,718 --> 00:29:23,449
You have done well from
first to last Mr. Sholto.

479
00:29:27,392 --> 00:29:31,089
My health is
somewhat fragile.

480
00:29:31,196 --> 00:29:37,032
I am compelled to
be a valetudinarian.

481
00:29:37,135 --> 00:29:39,330
Please?

482
00:29:50,515 --> 00:29:53,575
We dug up every
inch of the garden

483
00:29:53,685 --> 00:29:57,951
without discovering
anything.

484
00:29:58,056 --> 00:30:01,617
Brother Bartholomew is
such a clever fellow.

485
00:30:01,726 --> 00:30:03,557
Do you know how
he found out

486
00:30:03,662 --> 00:30:05,027
where the treasure was?

487
00:30:05,130 --> 00:30:07,189
Tell me.

488
00:30:07,299 --> 00:30:08,857
He made measurements
everywhere,

489
00:30:08,967 --> 00:30:10,298
all along the top,

490
00:30:10,402 --> 00:30:13,200
along the side, inside
and he found out

491
00:30:13,305 --> 00:30:16,638
he was 4 foot
out at the top.

492
00:30:16,741 --> 00:30:20,700
We found our father
made a false room

493
00:30:20,812 --> 00:30:24,771
So he smashed through
the lath and the plaster

494
00:30:24,883 --> 00:30:27,351
and there was the
treasure chest

495
00:30:27,452 --> 00:30:30,387
lying across the rafters.

496
00:30:30,489 --> 00:30:33,481
He has computed the
value of the treasure

497
00:30:33,592 --> 00:30:37,790
to be more than one
half million sterling.

498
00:30:37,896 --> 00:30:40,592
[scream]

499
00:30:40,699 --> 00:30:42,860
It's Mrs. Bernstone.

500
00:30:42,968 --> 00:30:45,903
Mrs. Bernstone is the
only lady in the house

501
00:30:46,004 --> 00:30:47,733
wait here.

502
00:30:59,050 --> 00:31:03,009
Oh, Mr. Thaddeus I'm
so glad you've come!

503
00:31:03,121 --> 00:31:05,681
I'm so glad
you've come, sir!

504
00:31:09,361 --> 00:31:13,422
What a strange place!

505
00:31:13,532 --> 00:31:15,193
It looks as if all
the moles in England

506
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:17,495
have been let
loose in it.

507
00:31:19,704 --> 00:31:22,366
There's something
amiss with Bartholomew

508
00:31:22,474 --> 00:31:24,965
Into the house!

509
00:31:38,189 --> 00:31:40,987
bless your
sweet, calm face.

510
00:31:41,092 --> 00:31:44,493
Oh, but I have been
sorely tried this day.

511
00:31:44,596 --> 00:31:46,587
How Mrs. Bernstone?

512
00:31:46,698 --> 00:31:48,893
Mr. Bartholomew shut
himself in his room

513
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,264
and I can't get a
word out of him.

514
00:31:51,369 --> 00:31:53,303
His bed hasn't
been slept in

515
00:31:53,405 --> 00:31:56,238
and he hasn't been
down for any food.

516
00:31:56,341 --> 00:31:58,468
I dare not disturb
him at his work.

517
00:31:58,577 --> 00:32:01,307
You know what he's like
when it's his work.

518
00:32:01,413 --> 00:32:03,745
Look after her
Miss Morstan.

519
00:32:09,654 --> 00:32:11,519
There, there do
try to calm down.

520
00:32:11,623 --> 00:32:13,386
Look I'm sure everything
will be all right.

521
00:32:13,491 --> 00:32:15,721
I do hope your right Miss.

522
00:32:15,827 --> 00:32:16,657
Sit down over there.

523
00:32:25,737 --> 00:32:27,102
Come.

524
00:32:38,383 --> 00:32:40,317
Which is the door?

525
00:33:14,185 --> 00:33:16,915
There's something
devilish in this, Watson.

526
00:33:53,625 --> 00:33:56,116
The sign of
the four again.

527
00:33:56,227 --> 00:33:58,024
What in God's name
does it all mean?

528
00:33:58,129 --> 00:34:00,689
It means murder.

529
00:34:04,169 --> 00:34:06,103
We brought the treasure
down there last night.

530
00:34:09,374 --> 00:34:10,841
Now its gone.

531
00:34:10,942 --> 00:34:12,842
What time is that?

532
00:34:12,944 --> 00:34:15,469
I don't know.

533
00:34:15,580 --> 00:34:20,677
I think six, or seven.

534
00:34:20,785 --> 00:34:25,347
I heard him lock the
door after I left.

535
00:34:25,457 --> 00:34:30,827
I must have been the last
person to see him alive.

536
00:34:30,929 --> 00:34:32,920
And now he's dead

537
00:34:37,035 --> 00:34:39,128
you think I did it?

538
00:34:39,237 --> 00:34:41,262
I didn't,
why should I,

539
00:34:41,372 --> 00:34:42,566
I wouldn't have
wanted you...

540
00:34:42,674 --> 00:34:44,335
I wouldn't have
asked you to...

541
00:34:44,442 --> 00:34:45,466
I'll go mad.

542
00:34:45,577 --> 00:34:46,839
Gentle, gently,
gentle Mr. Sholto.

543
00:34:46,945 --> 00:34:48,310
I suggest that
you go down to
the police station

544
00:34:48,413 --> 00:34:50,005
and tell them everything
that you know.

545
00:34:50,115 --> 00:34:52,481
We shall wait here
until you return.

546
00:34:52,584 --> 00:34:55,075
Holmes look at this.

547
00:34:55,186 --> 00:34:56,414
Careful!

548
00:34:56,521 --> 00:34:59,752
Forgive me,
its poisoned.

549
00:34:59,858 --> 00:35:01,849
Well Watson we
have a little time

550
00:35:01,960 --> 00:35:04,554
let's make the
most of it.

551
00:35:04,662 --> 00:35:06,289
Awe this is an
Insoluble mystery to me.

552
00:35:06,397 --> 00:35:07,728
It grows darker
instead of clearer.

553
00:35:07,832 --> 00:35:09,595
No, no, no, no it
clears every instant.

554
00:35:09,701 --> 00:35:10,998
I only require a
few missing links

555
00:35:11,102 --> 00:35:13,764
to have an entirely
connected case.

556
00:35:13,872 --> 00:35:15,271
Simple as the
case seems now

557
00:35:15,373 --> 00:35:18,137
there may be something
deeper underlying it.

558
00:35:18,243 --> 00:35:20,074
How did these
people come

559
00:35:20,178 --> 00:35:21,577
and how did they go?

560
00:35:21,679 --> 00:35:22,839
People?

561
00:35:22,947 --> 00:35:24,505
Well it takes more than
one, perhaps more than 2

562
00:35:24,616 --> 00:35:25,981
to remove a heavy
treasure chest

563
00:35:26,084 --> 00:35:28,018
from a place like this.

564
00:35:28,119 --> 00:35:30,553
The door hasn't been
opened since last night.

565
00:35:30,655 --> 00:35:32,885
So how about
these windows?

566
00:35:38,596 --> 00:35:41,326
Snibbed on the inside.

567
00:35:41,432 --> 00:35:43,525
No hinges.

568
00:35:43,635 --> 00:35:44,693
Roof quite out of reach.

569
00:35:44,803 --> 00:35:47,738
No drainpipe near.

570
00:35:47,839 --> 00:35:49,500
Yet someone has
entered this way look.

571
00:35:49,607 --> 00:35:51,006
Watson.

572
00:35:51,109 --> 00:35:54,169
See that a scuff
on the sill.

573
00:35:59,784 --> 00:36:03,015
Look at this Watson

574
00:36:03,121 --> 00:36:04,782
and this and this.

575
00:36:04,889 --> 00:36:06,516
This is a very
pretty demonstration.

576
00:36:06,624 --> 00:36:08,990
But that's not a footmark.

577
00:36:09,093 --> 00:36:10,560
Something much more
valuable to us.

578
00:36:10,662 --> 00:36:12,857
This is mark of
a boot and this

579
00:36:12,964 --> 00:36:17,833
this the mark of
the timber toe.

580
00:36:17,936 --> 00:36:20,370
It is a
wooden-legged man.

581
00:36:20,471 --> 00:36:22,939
And someone else.

582
00:36:23,041 --> 00:36:26,238
A very able and
efficient ally.

583
00:36:26,344 --> 00:36:28,505
Could you scale
that wall, Watson?

584
00:36:37,021 --> 00:36:38,318
Absolutely impossible.

585
00:36:38,423 --> 00:36:39,651
I aid it is so

586
00:36:39,757 --> 00:36:42,282
but suppose you
had a friend

587
00:36:42,393 --> 00:36:45,726
who lowered you
this good stout rope

588
00:36:45,830 --> 00:36:47,593
securing it first
to this ring.

589
00:36:47,699 --> 00:36:50,429
I think if you
were an active man,

590
00:36:50,535 --> 00:36:52,025
you'd be able
to swarm up,

591
00:36:52,136 --> 00:36:53,899
wooden leg and all.

592
00:36:54,005 --> 00:36:55,472
You would depart,
of course,

593
00:36:55,573 --> 00:36:57,438
in the same fashion,
and then your friend

594
00:36:57,542 --> 00:36:59,203
would pull up the rope,

595
00:37:02,614 --> 00:37:04,206
close the window,

596
00:37:04,315 --> 00:37:05,543
snib it on the inside,

597
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:08,380
and depart in the manner
he originally came.

598
00:37:11,155 --> 00:37:13,646
Well the thing grows more
unintelligible than ever.

599
00:37:13,758 --> 00:37:16,124
How about this
mysterious ally?

600
00:37:16,227 --> 00:37:17,819
How did he get
into the room?

601
00:37:17,929 --> 00:37:20,454
Yes, this ally.

602
00:37:20,565 --> 00:37:21,930
He lifts this case

603
00:37:22,033 --> 00:37:24,160
from the regions of
the commonplace.

604
00:37:24,269 --> 00:37:28,501
Well the door is locked;
the window inaccessible.

605
00:37:28,606 --> 00:37:29,766
The grate's too small.

606
00:37:29,874 --> 00:37:31,136
How then?

607
00:37:31,242 --> 00:37:32,641
You will not
follow my precept.

608
00:37:32,744 --> 00:37:33,938
How often have
I said to you

609
00:37:34,045 --> 00:37:35,307
that once you have
eliminated the impossible,

610
00:37:35,413 --> 00:37:36,675
whatever remains,

611
00:37:36,781 --> 00:37:38,043
however improbable,

612
00:37:38,149 --> 00:37:40,640
must be the truth?

613
00:37:45,189 --> 00:37:46,747
He must of come in
through the roof.

614
00:37:46,858 --> 00:37:48,450
Excellent Watson,
hold this lamp.

615
00:37:48,559 --> 00:37:51,084
Let us carry our research
to the room above

616
00:37:51,195 --> 00:37:54,995
the secret room in which
the treasure was found.

617
00:37:59,070 --> 00:38:01,538
The skylight.

618
00:38:12,417 --> 00:38:17,616
Holmes a child has
done this horrid thing.

619
00:38:17,722 --> 00:38:19,952
My memory failed me,

620
00:38:20,058 --> 00:38:22,925
for I should have been
able to foretell it.

621
00:38:23,027 --> 00:38:24,688
There is nothing we
can learn from here.

622
00:38:24,796 --> 00:38:25,820
Let us go down.

623
00:38:35,039 --> 00:38:37,166
What is your theory
about those footmarks?

624
00:38:37,275 --> 00:38:39,243
My dear Watson, try a
little analysis yourself.

625
00:38:39,344 --> 00:38:40,436
You know my methods.

626
00:38:40,545 --> 00:38:41,534
Apply them.

627
00:38:41,646 --> 00:38:42,670
I cannot conceive
of anything

628
00:38:42,780 --> 00:38:44,805
that will cover
the facts.

629
00:38:44,916 --> 00:38:46,577
You will soon.

630
00:39:03,968 --> 00:39:06,129
We're in luck.

631
00:39:06,237 --> 00:39:09,172
Our little ally

632
00:39:09,273 --> 00:39:11,571
has trod in
the creosote.

633
00:39:11,676 --> 00:39:14,236
[Voices from afar].

634
00:39:17,648 --> 00:39:20,310
Ahh, look at that.

635
00:39:20,418 --> 00:39:22,443
Quite a nice little
place you got here.

636
00:39:26,257 --> 00:39:27,656
Holmes!

637
00:39:27,759 --> 00:39:29,454
representatives of the law

638
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:31,255
unless I'm very,
very much mistaken.

639
00:39:31,362 --> 00:39:33,262
Now Watson

640
00:39:33,364 --> 00:39:35,059
before they come

641
00:39:35,166 --> 00:39:37,134
what do you make of
this poor fellow?

642
00:39:37,235 --> 00:39:39,999
The muscles are
stiff as a board.

643
00:39:40,104 --> 00:39:42,334
A state of extreme
contraction,

644
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:45,000
far exceeding the
usual rigor mortis.

645
00:39:45,109 --> 00:39:46,633
Quite so.

646
00:39:46,744 --> 00:39:48,644
Coupled with this
distortion of the face,

647
00:39:48,746 --> 00:39:50,441
the Hippocratic smile,

648
00:39:50,548 --> 00:39:53,540
risus sardonicus, as the
old writers called it,

649
00:39:53,651 --> 00:39:56,518
what would that
suggest to your mind?

650
00:39:56,621 --> 00:39:59,089
Death from a powerful
vegetable alkaloid

651
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:00,657
some strychnine-like
substance

652
00:40:00,758 --> 00:40:01,918
that produces tetanus.

653
00:40:04,095 --> 00:40:06,893
Well,

654
00:40:06,998 --> 00:40:08,431
to the right,

655
00:40:08,533 --> 00:40:11,093
come on along
gentleman to the right.

656
00:40:11,202 --> 00:40:13,193
Up these stairs.

657
00:40:17,875 --> 00:40:20,309
This thorn.

658
00:40:20,411 --> 00:40:22,538
old English thorn.

659
00:40:26,984 --> 00:40:28,747
I think it is not right
that Miss Morstan

660
00:40:28,853 --> 00:40:30,912
remain in this
stricken house.

661
00:40:31,022 --> 00:40:32,819
I suggest you slip away
and take her home Watson

662
00:40:32,924 --> 00:40:34,858
and then go to
3 Pinchin Lane,

663
00:40:34,959 --> 00:40:36,517
Lambeth and ask for Toby.

664
00:40:36,627 --> 00:40:37,787
3 Pinchin Lane.

665
00:40:37,895 --> 00:40:39,556
I'd rather have Toby's
help than that of the

666
00:40:39,664 --> 00:40:41,632
whole protective
force London.

667
00:40:45,203 --> 00:40:48,764
Well here's a
pretty business!

668
00:40:51,342 --> 00:40:53,640
Place is as full
as a rabbit-warren!

669
00:40:55,847 --> 00:40:58,338
I think you better
recollect me,

670
00:40:58,449 --> 00:41:02,044
Mr. Athelney Jones.

671
00:41:02,153 --> 00:41:07,455
Why, of course I do!

672
00:41:07,558 --> 00:41:11,255
Mr. Sherlock Holmes,
the theorist.

673
00:41:11,362 --> 00:41:14,126
I'll never forget that
you lectured us all

674
00:41:14,232 --> 00:41:17,133
about the Bishopgate
jewel case.

675
00:41:17,235 --> 00:41:20,796
True you set us on
the right track then

676
00:41:20,905 --> 00:41:22,372
I think you'll own now

677
00:41:22,473 --> 00:41:24,964
it is more by good luck
than good guidance.

678
00:41:25,076 --> 00:41:26,907
It was a piece of
very simple reasoning.

679
00:41:27,011 --> 00:41:28,911
Oh, come, now, come!

680
00:41:29,013 --> 00:41:31,880
Never be ashamed
to own up.

681
00:41:31,983 --> 00:41:37,717
But what is all this?

682
00:41:37,822 --> 00:41:39,084
It's a bad business!

683
00:41:39,190 --> 00:41:42,785
Bad business!

684
00:41:42,894 --> 00:41:46,557
Stern facts here

685
00:41:46,664 --> 00:41:48,598
no room for theories.

686
00:41:48,699 --> 00:41:51,133
It's lucky I happened
to be up at Norwood

687
00:41:51,235 --> 00:41:54,500
on another case when
I got the message.

688
00:41:54,605 --> 00:41:56,470
How do you think
this man died?

689
00:41:56,574 --> 00:41:58,337
This is not a case for
me to theorize over.

690
00:41:58,442 --> 00:42:00,603
No, no, no.

691
00:42:00,711 --> 00:42:02,269
Still, we can't deny

692
00:42:02,380 --> 00:42:05,781
you hit the nail on
the head sometimes.

693
00:42:08,386 --> 00:42:12,152
Door locked,
I understand.

694
00:42:12,256 --> 00:42:15,316
Jewels worth a
fortune missing.

695
00:42:15,426 --> 00:42:16,825
How were the windows?

696
00:42:16,928 --> 00:42:18,555
Fastened; but there was
a footstep on the sill.

697
00:42:18,663 --> 00:42:20,494
Windows fastened.

698
00:42:20,598 --> 00:42:23,897
Nothing to do with
it. It's common sense.

699
00:42:27,572 --> 00:42:31,440
Man could have died
in a fit I suppose.

700
00:42:31,542 --> 00:42:33,237
Ha!

701
00:42:33,344 --> 00:42:35,744
I have a theory.

702
00:42:35,846 --> 00:42:37,973
These flashes come
to me sometimes.

703
00:42:38,082 --> 00:42:40,778
Sergeant, outside
if you please.

704
00:42:40,885 --> 00:42:43,615
And you too, Mr. Sholto.

705
00:42:46,991 --> 00:42:49,425
What do you think
of this, Holmes?

706
00:42:49,527 --> 00:42:51,324
Sholto has confessed

707
00:42:51,429 --> 00:42:53,954
he was with his
brother last night.

708
00:42:54,065 --> 00:42:55,396
The brother died in a fit.

709
00:42:55,499 --> 00:42:56,830
Sholto walks off
with the treasure?

710
00:42:56,934 --> 00:42:58,060
How about that?

711
00:42:58,169 --> 00:42:59,568
Whereupon a dead man
very considerately

712
00:42:59,670 --> 00:43:03,470
gets up and locks the
door from the inside.

713
00:43:03,574 --> 00:43:07,670
Hum!

714
00:43:08,179 --> 00:43:11,740
There's a flaw
there somewhere.

715
00:43:11,849 --> 00:43:16,115
Let us apply common
sense to the matter.

716
00:43:16,220 --> 00:43:17,744
They were brothers

717
00:43:17,855 --> 00:43:20,346
there was a quarrel

718
00:43:20,458 --> 00:43:23,586
brother
Bartholomew dead

719
00:43:23,694 --> 00:43:24,991
jewels gone.

720
00:43:25,096 --> 00:43:27,326
And master Thaddeus

721
00:43:27,431 --> 00:43:30,366
evidently in a
disturbed state of mind.

722
00:43:30,468 --> 00:43:33,835
His appearance well,
not attractive.

723
00:43:33,938 --> 00:43:35,701
You see

724
00:43:35,806 --> 00:43:40,175
I'm weaving a web
around Thaddeus.

725
00:43:40,278 --> 00:43:43,975
The net begins to
close upon him.

726
00:43:44,081 --> 00:43:45,844
Jones

727
00:43:45,950 --> 00:43:48,248
that splinter,

728
00:43:50,621 --> 00:43:53,454
which I firmly believe
to be poisoned,

729
00:43:53,557 --> 00:43:55,787
that card and
that curiously
shaped instrument

730
00:43:55,893 --> 00:43:58,157
were lying there
on the table.

731
00:44:02,033 --> 00:44:04,763
Confirms my theory

732
00:44:04,869 --> 00:44:07,565
in every respect.

733
00:44:07,672 --> 00:44:09,299
The house is full of
Indian curiosities.

734
00:44:09,407 --> 00:44:11,341
All point to Thaddeus.

735
00:44:14,812 --> 00:44:16,677
But

736
00:44:16,781 --> 00:44:18,612
how did he escape?

737
00:44:21,786 --> 00:44:27,281
There is a trapdoor
in the roof Sergeant.

738
00:44:27,391 --> 00:44:31,452
May I ask Mr. Sholto
to step this way?

739
00:44:31,562 --> 00:44:35,828
You see facts are better
than theories, after all.

740
00:44:35,933 --> 00:44:38,026
My view of the
case is confirmed.

741
00:44:38,135 --> 00:44:39,602
There is a trapdoor

742
00:44:39,704 --> 00:44:41,137
communicating
with the roof,

743
00:44:41,238 --> 00:44:44,298
and it is partly open.

744
00:44:44,408 --> 00:44:47,707
It is I who opened it.

745
00:44:47,812 --> 00:44:50,280
Mr. Thaddeus Sholto, it
is my duty to inform you

746
00:44:50,381 --> 00:44:51,814
that anything you say
will be taken down

747
00:44:51,916 --> 00:44:54,180
and maybe used in
evidence against you.

748
00:44:54,285 --> 00:44:55,809
I arrest you in
the Queen's name

749
00:44:55,920 --> 00:44:59,617
as being concerned in the
death of your brother.

750
00:44:59,724 --> 00:45:01,351
I didn't I tell you

751
00:45:01,459 --> 00:45:03,984
Don't trouble
yourself, Mr. Sholto.

752
00:45:04,095 --> 00:45:05,392
I think that I can engage

753
00:45:05,496 --> 00:45:06,963
to clear you
of this charge.

754
00:45:07,064 --> 00:45:09,862
Don't promise too
much, Mr. Theorist.

755
00:45:09,967 --> 00:45:13,164
You may find it a harder
matter than you think.

756
00:45:13,270 --> 00:45:15,204
Not only will I
clear Mr. Sholto,

757
00:45:15,306 --> 00:45:16,830
but I will give
you a description

758
00:45:16,941 --> 00:45:19,375
of the 2 men who were
in this room last night.

759
00:45:19,477 --> 00:45:20,808
One was a poorly
educated man,

760
00:45:20,911 --> 00:45:22,071
strong,

761
00:45:22,179 --> 00:45:23,510
active,

762
00:45:23,614 --> 00:45:24,876
with his right leg off,

763
00:45:24,982 --> 00:45:26,950
wearing a stump worn
away on the inside.

764
00:45:27,051 --> 00:45:30,612
His left boot has a
coarse, square-toed sole

765
00:45:30,721 --> 00:45:33,986
it has an iron band
around the heel.

766
00:45:34,091 --> 00:45:36,082
He's much sunburned,
middle-aged

767
00:45:36,193 --> 00:45:37,888
and has a certain
amount of skin missing

768
00:45:37,995 --> 00:45:40,190
from the palm of one hand.

769
00:45:40,297 --> 00:45:43,198
And the other one?

770
00:45:43,300 --> 00:45:45,825
He's rather a
curious person.

771
00:45:48,038 --> 00:45:49,437
I hope before
long to be able to

772
00:45:49,540 --> 00:45:51,633
introduce you to
the pair of them.

773
00:45:59,383 --> 00:46:02,250
<i>Watson, go to 3
Pinchin Lane, London</i>

774
00:46:02,353 --> 00:46:04,412
<i>and ask for Toby.</i>

775
00:46:04,522 --> 00:46:05,955
<i>I'd rather have
Toby's help</i>

776
00:46:06,056 --> 00:46:08,422
<i>than that of the whole
detective force of London.</i>

777
00:46:45,763 --> 00:46:47,492
Mr. Toby?

778
00:46:51,101 --> 00:46:52,830
Mr. Toby?

779
00:46:52,937 --> 00:46:54,063
Mr. Toby?

780
00:46:54,171 --> 00:46:55,331
Get out of it.

781
00:46:55,439 --> 00:46:56,667
You drunken hooligan.

782
00:46:56,774 --> 00:46:58,503
Go on get out of it or
I'll turn my dogs on you.

783
00:46:58,609 --> 00:47:00,099
All 43 of them.

784
00:47:00,211 --> 00:47:03,180
I'm looking for Mr. Toby.

785
00:47:03,280 --> 00:47:04,542
I have a viper
in this bag,

786
00:47:04,648 --> 00:47:06,013
and I'll tip it
out over your 'ead

787
00:47:06,116 --> 00:47:07,413
if you don't hoof it!

788
00:47:07,518 --> 00:47:09,145
It's urgent
that I find him.

789
00:47:09,253 --> 00:47:10,720
I won't be argued with!

790
00:47:10,821 --> 00:47:13,119
1 , 2, 3 and down
comes the viper.

791
00:47:13,224 --> 00:47:15,055
I've come from Mr. Holmes.

792
00:47:15,159 --> 00:47:17,957
I've come from Mr.
Sherlock Holmes.

793
00:47:24,068 --> 00:47:27,265
Mr. Sherlock Holmes

794
00:47:27,371 --> 00:47:30,932
well who'd of
