00:53:59,897 --> 00:54:02,422
when he gets back.

890
00:54:02,532 --> 00:54:05,023
My what a rosy-cheeked
young rascal!

891
00:54:05,135 --> 00:54:06,762
Is there anything
you'd like Jack?

892
00:54:06,870 --> 00:54:09,031
I'd like a shillin'.

893
00:54:15,712 --> 00:54:17,907
A fine young lad you
got there, Mrs. Smith.

894
00:54:18,015 --> 00:54:20,347
Lor' bless you, sir, he
is that, and forward.

895
00:54:20,450 --> 00:54:22,247
He gets a'most too
much for me to manage,

896
00:54:22,352 --> 00:54:25,150
'specially when my man
is away days at a time.

897
00:54:25,255 --> 00:54:26,552
Awe it's a pity
about that.

898
00:54:26,657 --> 00:54:28,386
I was hoping to hire
a boat from him,

899
00:54:28,492 --> 00:54:29,550
a steam launch.

900
00:54:29,660 --> 00:54:30,888
Why, bless you, sir,

901
00:54:30,994 --> 00:54:32,291
it is in the steam
launch that he has gone.

902
00:54:32,396 --> 00:54:34,421
Aye' didn't like the
bloke who did the hire

903
00:54:34,531 --> 00:54:37,432
not at all, very rough,
