back of my hand.

1026
01:02:04,714 --> 01:02:07,239
I'm not going to
tell you again boy.

1027
01:02:41,651 --> 01:02:44,245
A nice little craft.

1028
01:02:44,354 --> 01:02:45,981
Aye, she's a
good boat this.

1029
01:02:46,089 --> 01:02:48,023
We built her right
in this yard.

1030
01:02:48,124 --> 01:02:49,785
Fastest boat on the river.

1031
01:02:49,893 --> 01:02:51,724
What she in for?

1032
01:02:51,828 --> 01:02:53,295
Repairs to her rudder.

1033
01:02:53,396 --> 01:02:54,590
That's the order.

1034
01:02:54,697 --> 01:02:56,494
I can't find anything
amiss with it.

1035
01:02:56,599 --> 01:02:58,123
I want her in the water

1036
01:02:58,234 --> 01:03:00,896
by six o'clock tonight.

1037
01:03:01,004 --> 01:03:03,905
Fully coaled and steam up.

1038
01:03:04,007 --> 01:03:06,635
Right Mr. Smith
she'll be ready.

1039
01:03:06,743 --> 01:03:09,143
Six o'clock sharp, mind,

1040
01:03:09,245 --> 01:03:13,443
for 2 gentlemen that'll
not be kept waiting.

1041
01:03:13,550 --> 01:03:15,381
Right.

1042
01:03:18,555 --> 01:03:20,546
It's this Norwood
case Doctor.

1043
01:03:20,657 --> 01:03:22,852
I have a great deal
to worry and try me.

1044
01:03:22,959 --> 01:03:26,326
And this case is a
very dark one too.

1045
01:03:26,429 --> 01:03:27,418
Thank you.

1046
01:03:27,530 --> 01:03:29,794
