Sherlock Holmes?

1064
01:04:10,907 --> 01:04:13,432
No but I'm
acting for him.

1065
01:04:13,543 --> 01:04:16,944
I've come about
this right here.

1066
01:04:17,046 --> 01:04:18,013
If you have any
information

1067
01:04:18,114 --> 01:04:19,843
you may give to me.

1068
01:04:19,949 --> 01:04:21,211
There's a reward.

1069
01:04:21,317 --> 01:04:24,115
Is it about the
steam launch, Aurora?

1070
01:04:24,220 --> 01:04:26,085
I'm telling no one but
Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

1071
01:04:26,189 --> 01:04:28,589
No, no; come inside.

1072
01:04:31,361 --> 01:04:33,795
I'm a police officer.

1073
01:04:33,897 --> 01:04:35,489
You look like one.

1074
01:04:35,598 --> 01:04:36,860
No you will be
recompensated

1075
01:04:36,966 --> 01:04:38,024
for your loss of time.

1076
01:04:38,134 --> 01:04:39,226
You will not have
long to wait.

1077
01:04:39,335 --> 01:04:41,530
Sit down.

1078
01:04:41,638 --> 01:04:42,764
Cigar Mr. Jones?

1079
01:04:42,872 --> 01:04:44,863
Oh, thank you for
you very much.

1080
01:04:51,281 --> 01:04:52,839
As I was saying Doctor,

1081
01:04:52,949 --> 01:04:54,143
I consider your friend

1082
01:04:54,250 --> 01:04:57,708
Mr. Sherlock Holmes is
a man not to be beat.

1083
01:04:57,820 --> 01:04:58,980
He would have made

1084
01:04:59,088 --> 01:05:00,578
the most promising
police officer.

1085
01:05:00,690 --> 01:05:01,884
I don't care
who knows it.

1086
01:05:01,991 --> 01:05:04,551
With a little
more discipline

1087
01:05:04,661 --> 01:05:07,095
and a lot less theory.

1088
01:05:07,196 --> 01:05:08,322
Thank you.

1089
01:05:08,431 --> 01:05:09,989
You might offer me one.

1090
01:05:14,170 --> 01:05:17,571
Oh, you rogue

1091
01:05:17,674 --> 01:05:19,437
you would have
made an actor

1092
01:05:19,542 --> 01:05:21,009
and a rare one.

1093
01:05:21,110 --> 01:05:23,772
You had the proper
workhouse cough,

1094
01:05:23,880 --> 01:05:25,404
and those weak
legs of yours

1095
01:05:25,515 --> 01:05:26,948
there worth 1 0
pounds each.

1096
01:05:27,050 --> 01:05:29,211
A police officer,
I'm flattered.

1097
01:05:29,319 --> 01:05:31,617
Jones I shall need
a police launch

1098
01:05:31,721 --> 01:05:33,154
at the Westminster steps.

1099
01:05:33,256 --> 01:05:34,518
The fastest you have.

1100
01:05:34,624 --> 01:05:36,091
2 stout men,
yourself, myself,

1101
01:05:36,192 --> 01:05:37,955
Watson all of us armed.

1102
01:05:38,061 --> 01:05:39,426
That is easily arranged.

1103
01:05:39,529 --> 01:05:41,292
I will telephone
the local station.

1104
01:05:50,840 --> 01:05:52,364
When we get to the tower

1105
01:05:52,475 --> 01:05:55,501
we'll stop opposite
of Jacobson's Yard.

1106
01:06:06,322 --> 01:06:07,983
How did you find
the Aurora then?

1107
01:06:08,091 --> 01:06:09,991
Well I have reasons that
the launch couldn't be

1108
01:06:10,093 --> 01:06:11,685
far often despite
of its invisibility.

1109
01:06:11,794 --> 01:06:15,059
So gentlemen,
where could it be?

1110
01:06:15,164 --> 01:06:17,394
Well out of the
water I suppose.

1111
01:06:17,500 --> 01:06:19,058
In a repair or
boat builders yard.

1112
01:06:19,168 --> 01:06:21,363
Exactly.

1113
01:06:41,791 --> 01:06:43,588
One of my boys is
waiting by the yard

1114
01:06:43,693 --> 01:06:45,388
to give us the signal.

1115
01:06:45,495 --> 01:06:47,156
You planned it all
very neatly Mr. Holmes

1116
01:06:47,263 --> 01:06:49,390
but if the affair
were in my hands

1117
01:06:49,499 --> 01:06:51,524
I should have a body
of police in the yard

1118
01:06:51,634 --> 01:06:53,363
and arrested them
when they came down.

1119
01:06:53,469 --> 01:06:55,096
Which would
have been never.

1120
01:06:55,204 --> 01:06:58,662
This man Small is a
pretty shrewd fellow.

1121
01:06:58,775 --> 01:07:00,037
Anything suspicious

1122
01:07:00,143 --> 01:07:02,703
and he would lie snug
for another week.

1123
01:07:04,213 --> 01:07:05,510
Sir?

1124
01:07:05,615 --> 01:07:07,139
We're opposite
Jacobson's Yard now,

1125
01:07:07,250 --> 01:07:08,740
shall we move
downstream a little.

1126
01:07:08,851 --> 01:07:12,719
No this mist may be
of an advantage to us.

1127
01:07:12,822 --> 01:07:15,313
We must lie low and wait.

1128
01:07:42,351 --> 01:07:43,648
Your boy's signaling,

1129
01:07:43,753 --> 01:07:45,914
I can see it plainly.

1130
01:08:02,605 --> 01:08:03,970
There's the Aurora

1131
01:08:04,073 --> 01:08:06,268
going like the devil

1132
01:08:06,375 --> 01:08:07,706
She's very fast.

1133
01:08:07,810 --> 01:08:09,243
I doubt if we
shall catch her.

1134
01:08:09,345 --> 01:08:10,812
We must catch her!

1135
01:08:10,913 --> 01:08:13,177
Pile it on, stokers!

1136
01:08:13,282 --> 01:08:14,408
I'll never forgive myself

1137
01:08:14,517 --> 01:08:16,644
if she proves to
have some use.

1138
01:08:22,158 --> 01:08:24,353
Faster, faster.

1139
01:08:24,460 --> 01:08:26,621
This is the fast
boat they've got.

1140
01:08:52,722 --> 01:08:53,814
Pile on the coals.

1141
01:08:53,923 --> 01:08:55,720
Stoke her.

1142
01:08:55,825 --> 01:08:57,417
We must have her.

1143
01:08:57,527 --> 01:08:59,552
Even if we burn the boat.

1144
01:09:30,760 --> 01:09:32,227
Keep the light steady.

1145
01:09:32,328 --> 01:09:34,421
I can almost make
out his companion.

1146
01:10:23,646 --> 01:10:25,204
We're gaining.

1147
01:10:39,996 --> 01:10:41,258
Pile it on, stoker.

1148
01:10:41,364 --> 01:10:44,925
Give it all the
steam we've got.

1149
01:10:45,034 --> 01:10:48,094
I think we
gained a little.

1150
01:10:48,204 --> 01:10:49,569
I'm sure of it.

1151
01:10:49,672 --> 01:10:50,934
Absolutely.

1152
01:11:02,985 --> 01:11:05,112
Point the light
more to the left.

1153
01:11:13,162 --> 01:11:14,493
Keep it steady.

1154
01:11:52,168 --> 01:11:57,196
What's happening
on that boat?

1155
01:11:57,306 --> 01:11:58,739
They're fighting
among themselves.

1156
01:11:58,841 --> 01:12:00,001
Tonga,

1157
01:12:00,109 --> 01:12:01,269
Tonga.

1158
01:12:05,948 --> 01:12:07,472
The peg leg.

1159
01:12:07,583 --> 01:12:09,050
Stop!

1160
01:12:09,151 --> 01:12:10,812
Police!

1161
01:12:10,920 --> 01:12:12,444
Cease you.

1162
01:12:12,555 --> 01:12:15,649
You can burn in hell

1163
01:12:15,758 --> 01:12:18,226
Stop!

1164
01:12:18,327 --> 01:12:23,390
The sign of four

1165
01:12:23,499 --> 01:12:25,660
Watson look.

1166
01:12:40,349 --> 01:12:42,510
What a face.

1167
01:14:49,545 --> 01:14:52,309
Wait

1168
01:14:52,414 --> 01:14:54,279
Wait.

1169
01:14:54,383 --> 01:14:56,817
Let him wear
himself out.

1170
01:15:36,992 --> 01:15:42,396
So Jonathan Small.

1171
01:15:42,498 --> 01:15:45,126
I am sorry it's
come to this.

1172
01:15:45,234 --> 01:15:48,465
And so am I sir.

1173
01:15:48,571 --> 01:15:51,005
But I give you my
word gentlemen

1174
01:15:51,106 --> 01:15:53,597
I never laid hands
on young Mr. Sholto.

1175
01:15:53,709 --> 01:15:55,176
Of course you didn't.

1176
01:15:55,277 --> 01:15:56,744
Your little friends
dart killed him

1177
01:15:56,845 --> 01:15:59,211
while he was still
climbing the rope.

1178
01:16:06,488 --> 01:16:09,355
Well you speak as if
you were there sir.

1179
01:16:19,735 --> 01:16:24,195
Well if it had been
old Major Sholto

1180
01:16:24,306 --> 01:16:28,766
I would have swung for
him with a light heart.

1181
01:16:28,877 --> 01:16:34,076
But to be lagged over
this young Sholto,

1182
01:16:34,183 --> 01:16:36,481
cursed heart.

1183
01:16:36,585 --> 01:16:38,052
You must make a
clean breast of it

1184
01:16:38,153 --> 01:16:41,213
if you do I may
be of use to you.

1185
01:16:43,192 --> 01:16:46,355
Quite a family party.

1186
01:16:46,462 --> 01:16:51,798
I reckon I'll pull
that flask myself.

1187
01:16:51,900 --> 01:16:56,428
Now, where are
you going Small?

1188
01:16:56,538 --> 01:16:59,200
The Esmeralda,
at Gravesend,

1189
01:16:59,308 --> 01:17:01,208
outward bound
for the Brazils.

1190
01:17:01,310 --> 01:17:02,777
And nearly made it.

1191
01:17:02,878 --> 01:17:04,277
Another man at the engines

1192
01:17:04,380 --> 01:17:07,907
and you'd never
have caught us.

1193
01:17:08,017 --> 01:17:11,612
Where's the key my man?

1194
01:17:11,720 --> 01:17:15,713
At the bottom
of the river.

1195
01:17:15,824 --> 01:17:17,223
Now look here,

1196
01:17:17,326 --> 01:17:19,157
we've had enough of
you tonight Small.

1197
01:17:19,261 --> 01:17:21,286
Bring the cuffs in
men, I'm warning you.

1198
01:17:21,397 --> 01:17:23,024
Its alright constable

1199
01:17:23,132 --> 01:17:24,963
When we leave the stacks.

1200
01:17:25,067 --> 01:17:27,228
I suggest that we go
back to Baker Street.

1201
01:17:27,336 --> 01:17:30,032
Well I think Miss
Morstan should be there.

1202
01:17:30,139 --> 01:17:33,006
Well that's not the
regulation way Mr. Holmes.

1203
01:17:33,108 --> 01:17:35,576
Well I can at least
promise you a nice,

1204
01:17:35,678 --> 01:17:38,476
warming drink.

1205
01:17:40,482 --> 01:17:42,211
Very well gentlemen.

1206
01:17:47,690 --> 01:17:50,750
Well Miss Morstan

1207
01:17:50,859 --> 01:17:52,759
I am pleased and proud

1208
01:17:52,861 --> 01:17:56,922
to have been able to bring
the thief to justice.

1209
01:17:57,032 --> 01:17:59,466
Justice?

1210
01:17:59,568 --> 01:18:02,196
The pretty justice.

1211
01:18:02,304 --> 01:18:05,034
Who's loot is this
if it is not ours?

1212
01:18:05,140 --> 01:18:07,574
Where is the justice
that I should give it up

1213
01:18:07,676 --> 01:18:09,439
to those who have
never owned it?

1214
01:18:09,545 --> 01:18:10,569
You forget Small

1215
01:18:10,679 --> 01:18:13,273
they know nothing
of this matter.

1216
01:18:13,382 --> 01:18:15,179
We cannot tell
how far justice

1217
01:18:15,284 --> 01:18:19,584
may have originally
been on your side.

1218
01:18:23,859 --> 01:18:26,487
No sir.

1219
01:18:26,595 --> 01:18:30,395
You have been
fair spoken to me,

1220
01:18:30,499 --> 01:18:32,091
though I can say
that it's you

1221
01:18:32,201 --> 01:18:33,930
that I have to thank

1222
01:18:34,036 --> 01:18:40,134
for these
bracelets on my wrists.

1223
01:18:40,242 --> 01:18:43,734
Still I bear no
grudge for that.

1224
01:18:43,846 --> 01:18:45,370
If you want to
hear my story

1225
01:18:45,481 --> 01:18:47,915
I have no wish
to hold it back.

1226
01:18:48,016 --> 01:18:51,543
And what I say to
you is God's truth,

1227
01:18:51,653 --> 01:18:53,678
every word of it.

1228
01:19:11,640 --> 01:19:13,801
When I was a lad

1229
01:19:13,909 --> 01:19:16,309
I took the Queen's
shilling and was

1230
01:19:16,412 --> 01:19:19,006
posted out to India
with the Third Buff's.

1231
01:19:23,485 --> 01:19:25,578
A crocodile
snapped this off

1232
01:19:25,687 --> 01:19:32,217
when I was bathing
in the Ganges.

1233
01:19:32,327 --> 01:19:33,988
The sawbones
had my stump

1234
01:19:34,096 --> 01:19:37,156
in the tar barrel
nice and quick.

1235
01:19:37,266 --> 01:19:41,202
I was young and strong.

1236
01:19:41,303 --> 01:19:44,602
We got my discharge
and this fellow...

1237
01:19:50,379 --> 01:19:53,371
it's been a good
support to me

1238
01:19:55,918 --> 01:19:59,649
so there I was a
cripple at 20.

1239
01:19:59,755 --> 01:20:02,223
But I liked it out there

1240
01:20:02,324 --> 01:20:04,622
so I found myself a
job as an overseer

1241
01:20:04,726 --> 01:20:07,092
on an Indigo farm.

1242
01:20:07,196 --> 01:20:12,065
I was on horseback all
day so that was fine.

1243
01:20:12,167 --> 01:20:15,295
But I was never
in luck for long,

1244
01:20:15,404 --> 01:20:16,837
without a note of warning

1245
01:20:16,939 --> 01:20:19,601
the great
mutiny was on us.

1246
01:20:19,708 --> 01:20:21,699
I came back to the farm
one evening to find

1247
01:20:21,810 --> 01:20:25,712
my master and all his
family be murdered.

1248
01:20:25,814 --> 01:20:27,213
I didn't wait.

1249
01:20:27,316 --> 01:20:30,410
On that same evening I
was in the Fort of Agra,

1250
01:20:30,519 --> 01:20:33,852
the nearest city still
held by the British.

1251
01:20:33,956 --> 01:20:36,288
The old Fort of Agra,

1252
01:20:36,391 --> 01:20:38,382
a queer place,

1253
01:20:38,494 --> 01:20:40,724
huge,

1254
01:20:40,829 --> 01:20:45,459
it's full of
passages and rooms

1255
01:20:45,567 --> 01:20:49,697
and more entrances
than you can count.

1256
01:20:49,805 --> 01:20:51,295
There were many gates

1257
01:20:51,406 --> 01:20:53,374
and because I was an
ex-soldier and British

1258
01:20:53,475 --> 01:20:55,170
they put me in charge
of one of them

1259
01:20:55,277 --> 01:20:57,108
and gave me a
couple of Sikkhs

1260
01:20:57,212 --> 01:20:58,907
who'd stayed loyal to us.

1261
01:20:59,014 --> 01:21:01,608
It was a lonely place.

1262
01:21:01,717 --> 01:21:05,778
My 2 Punjabis were
experienced, fighting men.

1263
01:21:05,888 --> 01:21:10,052
Kartar Singh and
Indarjit Singh.

1264
01:21:20,903 --> 01:21:22,268
Rebels?

1265
01:21:22,371 --> 01:21:23,895
No rebels.

1266
01:21:24,006 --> 01:21:25,871
The fort is safe.

1267
01:21:25,974 --> 01:21:29,933
There are no rebel
this side of the river.

1268
01:21:30,045 --> 01:21:31,637
You must be with us

1269
01:21:31,747 --> 01:21:34,580
or you must be
silenced forever.

1270
01:21:34,683 --> 01:21:36,344
With you how?

1271
01:21:36,451 --> 01:21:38,544
We want you to be rich,

1272
01:21:38,654 --> 01:21:42,818
which is why you British
came to this land.

1273
01:21:42,925 --> 01:21:45,291
Well I have no
objection of being rich.

1274
01:21:45,394 --> 01:21:48,488
Then swear by the
bones of your father

1275
01:21:48,597 --> 01:21:50,087
to raise no hand

1276
01:21:50,198 --> 01:21:52,530
and to speak no
word against us now

1277
01:21:52,634 --> 01:21:54,761
or ever afterwards

1278
01:21:54,870 --> 01:22:00,001
then you will have
quarter of the treasure.

1279
01:22:00,108 --> 01:22:01,837
But there are
only 3 of us.

1280
01:22:01,944 --> 01:22:04,344
Jagodish Singh my
foster brother

1281
01:22:04,446 --> 01:22:07,813
he must have his share.

1282
01:22:07,916 --> 01:22:13,513
There is no time
Sahib decide.

1283
01:22:13,622 --> 01:22:14,816
Well

1284
01:22:14,923 --> 01:22:18,120
provided the fort is
in no kind of danger

1285
01:22:18,226 --> 01:22:21,684
I swear.

1286
01:22:21,797 --> 01:22:25,494
What would you have
done Mr. Holmes?

1287
01:22:25,601 --> 01:22:26,727
I strongly suspect

1288
01:22:26,835 --> 01:22:30,464
I would have done
exactly as you did.

1289
01:22:30,572 --> 01:22:32,836
Yes I know the Sikkh.

1290
01:22:32,941 --> 01:22:35,375
He's not a man to
be trifled with.

1291
01:22:38,480 --> 01:22:41,040
One of our local Rajahs,

1292
01:22:41,149 --> 01:22:42,446
Rich as Croesus of course,

1293
01:22:42,551 --> 01:22:44,485
he'd gone in
with the rebels.

1294
01:22:44,586 --> 01:22:48,488
But... He wanted
to hedge his bet

1295
01:22:48,590 --> 01:22:51,753
just in case the
British came out on top.

1296
01:22:51,860 --> 01:22:54,385
So he made a plot to
get half his treasure

1297
01:22:54,496 --> 01:22:57,761
hidden in the Fort of Agra

1298
01:22:57,866 --> 01:22:59,390
sending one of
his men with it

1299
01:22:59,501 --> 01:23:01,628
in the guise
of a merchant

1300
01:23:01,737 --> 01:23:03,796
and Jagodish Singh

1301
01:23:03,905 --> 01:23:05,497
Kartar's brother

1302
01:23:05,607 --> 01:23:07,302
to be the guide.

1303
01:23:07,409 --> 01:23:10,037
They come challenging
sahib, in a major way

1304
01:23:10,145 --> 01:23:12,045
giving no caution to fear.

1305
01:23:12,147 --> 01:23:13,114
What then?

1306
01:23:13,215 --> 01:23:14,944
we do what has
to be done.

1307
01:23:26,962 --> 01:23:28,793
Who goes there?

1308
01:23:28,897 --> 01:23:31,422
A friend sahib.

1309
01:23:31,533 --> 01:23:33,865
A friend advance
and be recognized.

1310
01:23:37,606 --> 01:23:39,437
What have you with you?

1311
01:23:39,541 --> 01:23:44,808
A box sahib, old box.

1312
01:23:44,913 --> 01:23:47,074
Having some family papers.

1313
01:23:47,182 --> 01:23:51,209
No good to nobody
sahib only for myself.

1314
01:23:59,795 --> 01:24:04,664
Sahib, I'm no
ordinary beggar.

1315
01:24:04,766 --> 01:24:06,597
You will have money sahib.

1316
01:24:06,702 --> 01:24:09,500
and you comrades
sahib also.

1317
01:24:13,842 --> 01:24:16,402
Take him to the
main guardroom.

1318
01:24:39,634 --> 01:24:43,593
Never was a man
more compassed
round with death.

1319
01:25:16,171 --> 01:25:17,399
If that man had escaped

1320
01:25:17,506 --> 01:25:18,996
the whole affair
would have come out.

1321
01:25:19,107 --> 01:25:23,043
I should have been
shot most like.

1322
01:25:23,145 --> 01:25:29,015
Which of you would have
held back his musket?

1323
01:25:29,117 --> 01:25:32,644
Kartar was for
burning him,

1324
01:25:32,754 --> 01:25:34,551
that's there religion.

